item.title: ‘Karen’s’ Bunnings fight video goes viral
item.description: Outrageous footage of a woman refusing to wear a mask inside Bunnings has gone viral.

item.title: Tourist killed on Fraser Island
item.description: An international tourist has died on Fraser Island and another is fighting for life following a serious crash.

item.title: BLM protest thrown out of court
item.description: NSW Police has won its legal bid to stop a Black Lives Matter rally in Sydney going ahead next week, despite the judge acknowledging there was no evidence of COVID-19 transmission at a previous event.

item.title: SA cabinet ministers resign
item.description: THREE South Australian cabinet ministers have resigned over two parliamentary entitlement scandals.

item.title: Victoria records deadliest day of pandemic
item.description: Victoria has recorded 459 new coronavirus cases and 10 deaths on Sunday, with a man in his 40s one of the latest casualties.

item.title: Where the new NSW cases came from
item.description: New South Wales has recorded 14 new cases of coronavirus in the past 24 hours, bringing the total number of cases to 3479.

item.title: Treasurer defends JobKeeper cuts
item.description: Australia cannot afford to continue spending $11 billion a month on JobKeeper, Treasurer Josh Frydenberg says.

item.title: Men attacked with machetes, bats
item.description: A group of people armed with machetes and baseball bats have attacked two people in Sydney’s west.

item.title: Terror accused to front court
item.description: Jihadi bride Alo-Bridget Namoa has been charged for allegedly breaching her control order which was designed to keep the community safe.

item.title: Man charged with impersonating cop
item.description: A man has been charged after he allegedly tried to impersonate a police officer in an attempt to steal money from a Sydney business owner.
